1
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:43,130
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:48,020
Oh no.

4
00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:49,630
It's bleeding again.

5
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,160
It might have hit a vessel.

6
00:01:52,190 --> 00:01:52,880
Here.

7
00:01:53,210 --> 00:01:54,070
Tie it tighter.

8
00:01:55,390 --> 00:01:56,320
Look at his hand.

9
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,310
It's all purple.

10
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,509
Can it go any tighter?

11
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:00,800
Apply it on the proximal side.

12
00:02:01,010 --> 00:02:01,650
Who?

13
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,060
The upper arm,

14
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:04,190
near the shoulder. Here.

15
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,520
Tie it here. Tighten it.

16
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:18,880
Hang in there.

17
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,120
Yes. Right there.

18
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:22,780
Tighten it.

19
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:38,650
Stay in the car!

20
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:39,329
Don't move!

21
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:44,470
Captain.

22
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:46,300
What's wrong?

23
00:02:54,710 --> 00:02:55,570
So many people.

24
00:02:56,570 --> 00:02:57,829
What are they here for?

25
00:02:58,190 --> 00:02:58,880
Not sure.

26
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,280
Let's not go over there yet.

27
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:16,780
It's our truck.

28
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:28,620
Sangba!

29
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:29,640
What's going on?

30
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,620
Captain.

31
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,079
There are over 40 people there

32
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:33,280
trying to go into the mountains.

33
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,329
We stopped them,

34
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:36,010
but they refuse to turn back.

35
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,250
How many vehicles?

36
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,240
Three trucks.

37
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,070
The road is blocked,

38
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:39,530
but they're still shouting

39
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:40,470
to get in.

40
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,140
Are they armed?

41
00:03:44,970 --> 00:03:45,960
They haven't pulled out any guns,

42
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,890
but I'm not sure.

43
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,829
These people are very bold.

44
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:52,380
Zhacuo.

45
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:54,850
Get that boss out of the truck.

46
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:58,340
Get down!

47
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:05,520
Those people—

48
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:07,160
do you know them?

49
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,530
I don't know them.

50
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:10,030
You don't?

51
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:11,370
Do you know them? Speak!

52
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,200
Don't hit him!

53
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,900
Why are you pulling me?

54
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:14,560
Enough!

55
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:16,700
Stop it!

56
00:04:17,589 --> 00:04:18,220
Let go!

57
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:28,610
Those people are the buyers.

58
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:30,000
You arranged to meet

59
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,400
in the Uninhabited Zone.

60
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,120
They hand over the money,

61
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:33,770
take the pelts,

62
00:04:33,770 --> 00:04:35,100
and then head straight across the border,

63
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:35,720
right?

64
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:39,280
Speak!

65
00:04:48,070 --> 00:04:48,770
Get up!

66
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,500
We can't go over there

67
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,250
with those two

68
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,350
and a truckload of pelts.

69
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:03,270
What's there to be afraid of?
We charge through.

70
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:04,200
Charge through?

71
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,330
Those people

72
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,060
are here to buy pelts

73
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:06,920
from those two.

74
00:05:07,210 --> 00:05:08,170
There are dozens of them.

75
00:05:08,170 --> 00:05:09,570
What if they surround us?

76
00:05:09,890 --> 00:05:10,770
We have guns.

77
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:11,180
Yeah.

78
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,240
Don't we have the police with us?

79
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,300
Even the police can't just shoot them

80
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:14,060
like that.

81
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:23,400
Get in the car! Let's go help them!

82
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:24,960
We can't go over there!

83
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:31,850
Sangba,

84
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:34,460
you and the county militia stop them.

85
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:35,320
We'll fall back

86
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:36,920
and take a detour
out of the Uninhabited Zone.

87
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,450
Captain,

88
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:39,130
this is

89
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:41,080
the shortest way to Mazhi.

90
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,680
If we take a detour,

91
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,170
the road is harder

92
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:45,750
and it'll take

93
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:47,200
at least 2 more days.

94
00:05:48,570 --> 00:05:49,500
He is injured.

95
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,310
We can't take the risk.

96
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,270
Get in!

97
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:58,820
Sangba!

98
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,540
Hold them off!

99
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,190
Okay!

100
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,680
What took you so long?

101
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,960
My mom made me put mousse in my hair.

102
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:27,090
It was so uncomfortable.

103
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:28,420
I washed my hair at home.

104
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:29,870
Sorry

105
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:31,060
to keep you waiting.

106
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:32,250
The movie

107
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:33,909
started over half an hour ago.

108
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:43,070
Then let's watch the next one.

109
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:45,420
I'm hungry anyway. Let's eat first.

110
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:46,820
But I want to see this one.

111
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:47,530
[Farewell My Concubine]

112
00:06:47,530 --> 00:06:48,320
It's an opera.

113
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,650
What's so good about it?

114
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:51,390
True Lies

115
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,000
is much better.

116
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,600
It's an American blockbuster.
Very exciting.

117
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:55,900
Hurry up.

118
00:06:55,930 --> 00:06:56,790
It's starting.

119
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:07,180
You'd better not eat sunflower seeds.

120
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,000
Why?

121
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:12,410
Doing that in a movie theater

122
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:13,600
shows no class.

123
00:07:13,730 --> 00:07:14,200
Look.

124
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:17,730
Isn't everyone doing it?

125
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:20,850
Want some?

126
00:07:22,770 --> 00:07:23,830
Eat them yourself.

127
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,600
You know what?

128
00:07:28,070 --> 00:07:29,540
Foreigners

129
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:31,060
eat popcorn when watching movies.

130
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,790
Who hasn't had popcorn before?

131
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:38,190
Not the kind from the "black cannon."

132
00:07:38,270 --> 00:07:39,610
Buttered popcorn.

133
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:40,700
Have you tried it?

134
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:46,180
No.

135
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,080
I'll buy you some next time.

136
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,060
Do you still want the soda?

137
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:56,090
Does drinking soda make you look unclassy?

138
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,520
That is fine.

139
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:31,970
No!

140
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,590
Stop!

141
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,500
Here. Watch these two!

142
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,390
How are you doing?

143
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:49,720
Take a break.

144
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:50,580
Here.

145
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,320
Zhacuo.

146
00:08:55,950 --> 00:08:57,030
I'll go give it a try.

147
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:57,620
Okay.

148
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,250
Ready?

149
00:08:58,550 --> 00:08:59,080
Ready.

150
00:08:59,140 --> 00:08:59,610
Okay!

151
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,570
I'll drive then!

152
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:00,940
Okay!

153
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:01,460
Drive!

154
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:03,580
One, two, go!

155
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:04,840
Okay!

156
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:07,860
One, two, three!

157
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:12,990
Push harder!

158
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:13,870
Let's go!

159
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:16,230
One, two, go!

160
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,300
Come help!

161
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:20,160
Let's pull together!

162
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:20,650
Come!

163
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:21,930
One, two!

164
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,670
One, two, three!

165
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,400
One, two, three!

166
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:39,880
Does it hurt badly?

167
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,010
It's okay.

168
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:44,100
After we get back and go to the hospital,

169
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,500
I'll be fine
after a couple of days of shots.

170
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:48,290
How many days will this route take?

171
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:48,940
Two days.

172
00:09:50,420 --> 00:09:51,480
Three days at most.

173
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:53,800
I've been this way.

174
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:57,270
Follow the river,

175
00:09:58,570 --> 00:09:59,980
cut across the mountains to the north,

176
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:01,440
and we'll hit the highway,

177
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:03,930
just bypassing the checkpoint.

178
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:06,170
Why is Zhacuo's team

179
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:07,360
not catching up?

180
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,320
Han.

181
00:10:16,260 --> 00:10:17,260
Move aside first.

182
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:27,580
Here.

183
00:10:32,730 --> 00:10:33,200
Okay.

184
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,030
Go drive.

185
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:36,700
Come on.

186
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:38,050
Come and help.

187
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:38,770
Get up!

188
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:40,700
Get up!

189
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,100
Go!

190
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:45,830
Push the car!

191
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:46,240
Go!

192
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,750
One, two, three!

193
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:54,020
Let's go, Zhacuo!

194
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:54,760
Zhacuo!

195
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,440
One, two, three!

196
00:10:58,460 --> 00:10:59,200
Go.

197
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,680
One, two, go!

198
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:02,370
Zhacuo!

199
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:04,740
One, two, go!

200
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:11,510
Get down!

201
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:12,670
Get down!

202
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:14,630
Get down!

203
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,050
Han!

204
00:11:20,940 --> 00:11:22,340
The truck's stuck again.

205
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,360
It keeps sinking as we go.

206
00:11:27,370 --> 00:11:28,390
It's too heavy.

207
00:11:28,890 --> 00:11:29,890
We just dug it out.

208
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:32,390
It's been a whole day,

209
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:34,450
and we barely covered 10 kilometers.

210
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:36,810
Are you two holding up?

211
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:38,530
We're okay.

212
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:42,270
Let's set up the tents.

213
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:43,980
Everyone is exhausted.

214
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,720
We can keep going!

215
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:47,220
We can keep going!

216
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:48,690
We can't stop!

217
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:52,960
He's arm is still injured.

218
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:55,280
Everyone up!

219
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:56,880
Get in the car!

220
00:12:02,370 --> 00:12:03,300
Set up the tents!

221
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:24,250
Liquor.

222
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:40,920
Have some.

223
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:42,350
Thanks.

224
00:12:42,490 --> 00:12:43,550
Careful, it's hot.

225
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:49,040
Alright.

226
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,760
He Qingyuan has a serious fever.

227
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:09,870
The Captain can't get up.

228
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,700
We can't go on like this.

229
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:17,460
Listen.

230
00:13:18,170 --> 00:13:19,080
Let Han take the Captain

231
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,250
and He Qingyuan

232
00:13:20,420 --> 00:13:21,660
go ahead in the jeep.

233
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:22,440
Zhacuo,

234
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:24,770
you and I stay and deal with the truck.

235
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:25,740
That won't work.

236
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:27,250
With just the two of you,

237
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:28,200
how are you supposed to dig it out?

238
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:28,790
If we keep you here,

239
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:30,080
can you help dig the truck out?

240
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,810
We'd have to look after you too.

241
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:41,170
The truck is too heavy.

242
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:42,600
We won't get far

243
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:44,150
before it gets stuck again.

244
00:13:44,650 --> 00:13:45,650
All our energy and strength

245
00:13:45,650 --> 00:13:45,980
have been spent

246
00:13:45,980 --> 00:13:47,360
on digging it out.

247
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:52,010
We're almost out of water and rations.

248
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,500
You know better than I do what'll happen

249
00:13:57,870 --> 00:13:59,470
if we keep dragging this out.

250
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:03,650
No.

251
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:07,100
We're still far from the highway.

252
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:09,460
What if we leave you here

253
00:14:10,510 --> 00:14:12,110
and you run into sandstorms,

254
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,340
blizzards,

255
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:14,870
or poachers?

256
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:15,790
That's still better than all of us

257
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,450
getting stuck here and dying.

258
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,670
As long as someone makes it out,

259
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:29,910
there's hope.

260
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,300
How about this?

261
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:52,580
Bai Ju will drive.

262
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,340
Let's take those two

263
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:56,200
out first.

264
00:14:58,820 --> 00:14:59,550
Zhacuo,

265
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:01,940
you and Han

266
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,550
find a way to drive the truck out.

267
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:05,650
Okay.

268
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,960
I don't know the way.

269
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:08,630
If, on the way,

270
00:15:08,630 --> 00:15:10,080
you two patients fall asleep,

271
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:10,880
I won't be able to

272
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,140
drive out on my own.

273
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:15,980
Zhacuo.

274
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:18,600
Let's stick together.

275
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:19,890
You'll get me

276
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:20,550
out of here,

277
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,480
right?

278
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:25,820
Yes.

279
00:15:53,310 --> 00:15:54,390
If you get lost,

280
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,840
look for the North Star.

281
00:15:58,980 --> 00:15:59,690
If

282
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:00,860
it's cloudy,

283
00:16:02,370 --> 00:16:03,970
look at the ice on the ground—

284
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:06,050
the side

285
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:08,040
that melts faster

286
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,000
is south.

287
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,080
And remember,

288
00:16:13,210 --> 00:16:15,640
most snow mountains and big rivers

289
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,100
run east to west.

290
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:19,720
Okay.

291
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:23,460
Don't just follow the tire tracks—

292
00:16:24,370 --> 00:16:26,030
they could be your own.

293
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:26,890
Don't worry.

294
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:28,750
Didn't you say

295
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:31,190
that we have to finish the path

296
00:16:31,270 --> 00:16:32,730
to reach our destination?

297
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,460
If there's an emergency,

298
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:38,650
don't hesitate.

299
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:40,280
Shoot immediately.

300
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,050
I promise.

301
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,180
It's cold at night.

302
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,340
Keep this.

303
00:17:06,849 --> 00:17:08,250
There's half a roll left.

304
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:08,960
On the road,

305
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:09,920
if it feels loose,

306
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,119
tighten it yourself.

307
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:11,750
Got it?

308
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,900
Aren't you going with us?

309
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:16,900
There's no room in the car.

310
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,240
I'll stay and watch over things.

311
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:38,030
You must

312
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:39,480
make it out alive.

313
00:17:58,290 --> 00:17:58,890
Take care.

314
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:38,700
Zhacuo!

315
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,250
Take care of them.

316
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,510
A sandstorm's coming.

317
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:28,100
Hurry! Hurry!

318
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:28,640
Isn't it

319
00:20:28,940 --> 00:20:29,670
hailing?

320
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:30,900
How is there a sandstorm coming?

321
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:31,400
The weather in the Uninhabited Zone

322
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,280
is unpredictable.

323
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:33,180
Here, cover up.

324
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:34,780
Check the stuff in the back!

325
00:21:35,910 --> 00:21:36,630
The stuff in the back!

326
00:21:36,630 --> 00:21:37,410
Go check it!

327
00:21:37,990 --> 00:21:38,660
Hurry!

328
00:21:47,420 --> 00:21:48,480
The tents are gone!

329
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:50,350
The tents are gone?

330
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:50,910
Yeah.

331
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,260
Hurry up and check

332
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:53,460
what else is missing.

333
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:00,550
Gas,

334
00:22:01,210 --> 00:22:02,010
water...

335
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:03,570
Pelts.

336
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,680
One,

337
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:06,480
two, three.

338
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:13,580
No rations left?

339
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:14,550
No rations left!

340
00:22:15,090 --> 00:22:16,050
Check it out! Hurry!

341
00:22:16,050 --> 00:22:17,880
Check if there's food underneath.

342
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:18,660
Zhacuo, let's go!

343
00:22:18,660 --> 00:22:19,790
Let's find the food!

344
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,940
The blowtorch is here.

345
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:32,840
Only a little fuel left.

346
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,040
Did you find the food?

347
00:22:38,220 --> 00:22:39,410
I remember

348
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,840
there are some in the cab.

349
00:22:41,660 --> 00:22:42,920
I ate half a flatbread.

350
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,030
There are 3 buns left.

351
00:22:47,790 --> 00:22:48,510
Three?

352
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,330
One for each?

353
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:53,010
It won't last the day.

354
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:56,480
Keep looking.

355
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:08,010
Where else can we look?

356
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:10,160
Let's go.

357
00:23:11,070 --> 00:23:11,940
Before dark,

358
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:14,520
we need to find shelter from the wind.

359
00:23:15,140 --> 00:23:16,070
W-Wait, wait.

360
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:21,250
Is that... is that a sheep?

361
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,580
It's a baby Tibetan antelope.

362
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,140
It probably got separated

363
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:32,250
from the herd during the sandstorm.

364
00:23:33,010 --> 00:23:33,770
What do we do?

365
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:38,270
It's a wild animal.

366
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,660
Can we take it with us?

367
00:23:42,010 --> 00:23:43,570
A baby antelope alone

368
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:45,900
won't survive.

369
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:51,970
Let's take it for now.

370
00:24:18,210 --> 00:24:18,940
Stop the car.

371
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,970
They could be poachers.

372
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,060
They probably ran out of fuel

373
00:24:29,060 --> 00:24:30,260
and couldn't get out.

374
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,200
I know.

375
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:35,420
They could also be

376
00:24:35,420 --> 00:24:36,850
runaway fossickers.

377
00:24:40,310 --> 00:24:41,250
Get a few buns.

378
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:44,510
We don't have many left.

379
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,440
Get some.

380
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:48,330
It's a waste to give the buns to them.

381
00:24:48,330 --> 00:24:48,960
Within hundreds of kilometers,

382
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:50,020
they won't get out.

383
00:24:50,460 --> 00:24:50,790
By then,

384
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:51,360
no one will have food.

385
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,090
Then it comes out of your share.

386
00:25:57,090 --> 00:25:57,750
That's all?

387
00:25:58,110 --> 00:25:58,770
That's all.

388
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,070
Zhacuo.

389
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,760
Is this an old sheep pen

390
00:26:08,060 --> 00:26:09,410
that was torn down?

391
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:10,750
No, no.

392
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:13,870
It was for hunting years ago.

393
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,420
See the two rows of stones?

394
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:17,880
That opening is wider,

395
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,280
and this one is narrower.

396
00:26:19,650 --> 00:26:21,910
When an animal accidentally wanders in,

397
00:26:23,100 --> 00:26:24,760
it can only follow the stones.

398
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,640
They put a pile of traps here,

399
00:26:27,850 --> 00:26:29,650
and that's how they caught them.

400
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:31,310
Like this?

401
00:26:31,770 --> 00:26:32,520
Yeah.

402
00:26:32,850 --> 00:26:34,450
That's such a clever method.

403
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:35,920
It's too much trouble.

404
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:37,780
Nowadays they just use guns.

405
00:26:47,830 --> 00:26:49,150
Stay here.

406
00:26:49,180 --> 00:26:50,520
I'll get you some grass.

407
00:27:23,770 --> 00:27:24,480
Look!

408
00:27:24,570 --> 00:27:26,030
It was left by the Captain!

409
00:27:28,050 --> 00:27:28,680
Give it to me.

410
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:29,180
Look.

411
00:27:33,690 --> 00:27:34,250
[You must take care of yourselves!]

412
00:27:34,250 --> 00:27:36,250
That's the Captain's handwriting.

413
00:27:38,010 --> 00:27:39,670
They passed through here too.

414
00:27:40,220 --> 00:27:42,220
Looks like we're on the right track.

415
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,570
Are those vultures?

416
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:53,770
Yes.

417
00:27:56,900 --> 00:27:58,240
Will they bite us?

418
00:27:59,110 --> 00:27:59,700
No.

419
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:02,560
If vultures

420
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:03,880
are flying low,

421
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:04,980
it means someone

422
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:07,040
or some animal nearby is about to die.

423
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,500
They're waiting for the carcass.

424
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,130
Someone's stuck in quicksand.

425
00:28:55,710 --> 00:28:56,330
Don't go over there!

426
00:28:56,330 --> 00:28:56,720
Come back! Come back!

427
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,400
There's quicksand!

428
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:58,000
Come back!

429
00:28:58,380 --> 00:28:58,980
Come back!

430
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:02,640
Wake up!

431
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,360
Can you speak?

432
00:29:08,900 --> 00:29:10,290
We need to pull him out.

433
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:12,460
I'll get the rope.

434
00:29:16,700 --> 00:29:17,300
My friend!

435
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:21,050
Are you okay?

436
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:28,290
Don't be afraid!

437
00:29:28,710 --> 00:29:30,170
We'll save you right away!

438
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:30,970
Don't move!

439
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,590
Zhacuo!

440
00:29:38,990 --> 00:29:39,850
Don't panic!

441
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:40,330
Hurry!

442
00:29:40,790 --> 00:29:41,310
Coming.

443
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:42,480
Hurry.

444
00:29:42,850 --> 00:29:43,250
Here.

445
00:29:44,350 --> 00:29:45,270
Don't move!

446
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:47,750
Grab the rope!

447
00:29:51,050 --> 00:29:51,420
Okay.

448
00:29:51,530 --> 00:29:51,990
Come on.

449
00:29:52,070 --> 00:29:52,480
Grab it!

450
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:53,280
Hold on tight!

451
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:54,460
Come on!

452
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:54,830
Come on!

453
00:29:54,830 --> 00:29:55,380
One,

454
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:56,050
two,

455
00:29:56,290 --> 00:29:56,570
three!

456
00:29:56,570 --> 00:29:57,100
Let's go!

457
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:02,270
No, no.

458
00:30:02,610 --> 00:30:03,410
It won't work.

459
00:30:05,700 --> 00:30:06,270
What are you doing?

460
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:06,680
Here.

461
00:30:10,310 --> 00:30:11,610
You'll fall into it too.

462
00:30:11,610 --> 00:30:12,590
I'm light.

463
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:13,960
Hold me tight later.

464
00:30:15,210 --> 00:30:15,920
Tighter.

465
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:17,540
Don't move!

466
00:30:17,570 --> 00:30:18,350
Alright, alright. Go now.

467
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:18,810
Alright.

468
00:30:18,810 --> 00:30:19,240
Alright.

469
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,370
Give me the canteen.

470
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:28,790
Don't move!

471
00:30:29,610 --> 00:30:30,400
Be careful!

472
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:31,610
Don't worry.

473
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:48,940
Don't move.

474
00:30:54,770 --> 00:30:55,700
Don't be afraid.

475
00:31:10,770 --> 00:31:11,250
Here.

476
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:13,310
Have some water.

477
00:31:16,110 --> 00:31:16,970
Lift your head.

478
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,010
Did you get it?

479
00:31:28,090 --> 00:31:29,150
I'll hold on to you.

480
00:31:29,250 --> 00:31:29,920
Don't move.

481
00:31:37,350 --> 00:31:38,000
Okay!

482
00:31:38,330 --> 00:31:38,940
Pull!

483
00:31:39,030 --> 00:31:40,570
One, two, go!

484
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:42,740
One, two, go!

485
00:31:44,050 --> 00:31:45,570
It's not working! Pull again!

486
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:46,240
Pull!

487
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:47,680
Harder!

488
00:31:49,860 --> 00:31:51,040
One, two!

489
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:52,610
Pull again!

490
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,380
Pull!

491
00:31:55,670 --> 00:31:56,730
Wait a second!

492
00:31:58,980 --> 00:31:59,980
It's not working.

493
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:11,440
Hang in there. It's almost done.

494
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:23,200
Don't move.

495
00:32:27,830 --> 00:32:29,030
Loosen the rope a bit.

496
00:32:29,090 --> 00:32:29,680
Okay!

497
00:32:42,140 --> 00:32:42,820
Ready!

498
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:47,160
Come on!

499
00:32:47,250 --> 00:32:48,050
Pull hard!

500
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:50,420
One, two, three, pull!

501
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:52,890
Pull!

502
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:55,350
Again!

503
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:57,460
Pull!

504
00:32:59,030 --> 00:32:59,700
Pull!

505
00:33:00,260 --> 00:33:01,090
Harder!

506
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,520
Keep pulling!

507
00:33:04,770 --> 00:33:06,920
One, two, three!

508
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:08,770
Quick!

509
00:33:09,770 --> 00:33:11,110
One, two!

510
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:12,030
Pull!

511
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:13,250
Pull!

512
00:33:15,330 --> 00:33:16,980
One, two, pull!

513
00:33:17,350 --> 00:33:17,980
Harder!

514
00:33:21,550 --> 00:33:22,530
Pull!

515
00:33:24,420 --> 00:33:25,110
Again!

516
00:33:25,790 --> 00:33:26,760
Pull!

517
00:33:27,110 --> 00:33:29,920
One, two, three!

518
00:33:29,940 --> 00:33:30,830
Almost out!

519
00:33:31,030 --> 00:33:33,270
One, two, three!

520
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:34,790
One!

521
00:33:35,570 --> 00:33:36,180
Again!

522
00:33:36,420 --> 00:33:38,550
One, two, three!

523
00:33:39,590 --> 00:33:40,360
Wait!

524
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:50,380
Come on! Pull!

525
00:34:34,570 --> 00:34:35,500
Have some water.

526
00:34:43,630 --> 00:34:44,760
Have some hot water.

527
00:34:44,929 --> 00:34:45,429
Here.

528
00:34:53,010 --> 00:34:53,730
Why did you come into

529
00:34:53,730 --> 00:34:54,989
the Uninhabited Zone?

530
00:34:55,650 --> 00:34:56,710
To hunt antelopes?

531
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:58,380
No.

532
00:35:00,430 --> 00:35:01,400
Mining gold...

533
00:35:02,980 --> 00:35:04,050
With my brother...

534
00:35:04,940 --> 00:35:06,130
A fossicker.

535
00:35:07,110 --> 00:35:07,550
Then why did you

536
00:35:07,550 --> 00:35:08,340
get out alone?

537
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:09,600
Where is your brother?

538
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:13,270
He got taken.

539
00:35:14,860 --> 00:35:16,000
He was taken away.

540
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:17,880
He was taken away?

541
00:35:18,510 --> 00:35:19,650
By whom?

542
00:35:23,500 --> 00:35:24,340
I don't know.

543
00:35:25,460 --> 00:35:26,860
They had guns.

544
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,090
Guns?

545
00:35:29,650 --> 00:35:30,630
That's similar to what I faced

546
00:35:30,630 --> 00:35:31,900
when I first came in.

547
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,350
Do you know

548
00:35:34,380 --> 00:35:35,510
where they took him?

549
00:35:43,670 --> 00:35:44,670
He fainted again.

550
00:36:18,170 --> 00:36:18,800
Captain.

551
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:20,530
Are you cold?

552
00:36:25,670 --> 00:36:26,230
Captain?

553
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:29,530
Captain?

554
00:36:32,860 --> 00:36:33,440
He!

555
00:36:34,070 --> 00:36:34,690
He!

556
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:39,090
What did you two do?

557
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:41,160
We didn't do anything!

558
00:36:41,530 --> 00:36:42,730
They just passed out!

559
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:44,040
Exactly.

560
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:10,710
Han.

561
00:37:13,380 --> 00:37:15,510
Is it okay to drink with a stomachache?

562
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,720
It'll warm you up.

563
00:37:18,900 --> 00:37:19,690
I'm fine.

564
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:22,590
Are you guys cold?

565
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,050
I'm not cold.

566
00:37:29,010 --> 00:37:29,900
Keep it on.

567
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,340
How is He?

568
00:37:32,130 --> 00:37:33,190
Let me check on him.

569
00:37:38,630 --> 00:37:39,570
Captain.

570
00:37:39,670 --> 00:37:40,710
He's burning up.

571
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:42,650
Let's go now.

572
00:37:42,980 --> 00:37:43,500
Okay.

573
00:39:24,780 --> 00:39:25,400
Duojie.

574
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:32,130
Duojie.

575
00:39:33,570 --> 00:39:34,670
Uncle...

576
00:39:36,210 --> 00:39:37,710
Get... Director Zhang.

577
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:43,940
Okay.

578
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:58,420
He Qingyuan has a gunshot wound
to his upper left arm.

579
00:39:58,420 --> 00:39:59,480
He was hit 3 days ago

580
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:00,700
and the bullet hasn't been removed.

581
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:01,880
He's been sent for X‑rays.

582
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:02,670
Plasma is ready,

583
00:40:02,670 --> 00:40:03,570
and he'll get a transfusion right after.

584
00:40:03,570 --> 00:40:04,630
What about Duojie?

585
00:40:04,730 --> 00:40:05,570
He said it was gastritis,

586
00:40:05,570 --> 00:40:06,190
an old problem.

587
00:40:06,190 --> 00:40:07,880
But it looks more like
a gastric ulcer to me.

588
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:09,590
There may be more than one ulcer site.

589
00:40:09,590 --> 00:40:10,340
What about the others?

590
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:10,880
Are they in danger?

591
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:11,340
The rest

592
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:12,360
are suffering from dehydration
and hypothermia

593
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:12,880
to varying degrees.

594
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:14,130
They're all being monitored.

595
00:40:14,130 --> 00:40:14,990
Where is Bai Ju?

596
00:40:15,190 --> 00:40:15,860
Bai Ju?

597
00:40:16,610 --> 00:40:17,590
I didn't see her.

598
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:21,870
Glucose, painkillers,

599
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:23,500
gauze, alcohol,

600
00:40:24,030 --> 00:40:24,830
and morphine.

601
00:40:25,150 --> 00:40:26,280
Give me another box of cardiac stimulants.

602
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:26,780
Okay.

603
00:40:29,420 --> 00:40:30,950
This antibiotic is for you.

604
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,000
Now that you're back,

605
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:32,880
you need a gastroscopy

606
